00:13:13.970 --> 00:13:16.160
And actually there's
20, but I'm not

00:13:16.160 --> 00:13:18.180
going to get into
the fine details.

00:13:18.180 --> 00:13:20.605
There's perfect-flowered,
like a rose bush.

00:13:20.605 --> 00:13:23.275
You've got male and
female in the same flower.

00:13:23.275 --> 00:13:26.450
A bee only has to move the
pollen from the male part

00:13:26.450 --> 00:13:30.790
to the female part, maybe a
quarter of an inch or less.

00:13:30.790 --> 00:13:33.860
The pollen is typically
sticky and large,

00:13:33.860 --> 00:13:35.810
not causing a lot of allergies.

00:13:35.810 --> 00:13:39.270
However, there are exceptions.

00:13:39.270 --> 00:13:45.140
Monoecious, monoecious trees
have like typically one branch

00:13:45.140 --> 00:13:48.940
is all male, one is all female.

00:13:48.940 --> 00:13:52.020
These used to trap a
lot of their own pollen.

00:13:52.020 --> 00:13:54.780
The parking lot where
we're parked in today

00:13:54.780 --> 00:13:58.540
