00:28:00.830 --> 00:28:02.650
And the more I think
about it, I liked

00:28:02.650 --> 00:28:06.860
that because a female
tree is not just there.

00:28:06.860 --> 00:28:09.180
It's not that it
doesn't produce.

00:28:09.180 --> 00:28:12.480
It's also pulling
pollen out of the air.

00:28:12.480 --> 00:28:16.670
Quickly on how that happens, you
have a female the and her roots

00:28:16.670 --> 00:28:17.920
are in the ground.

00:28:17.920 --> 00:28:20.500
She's grounded.

00:28:20.500 --> 00:28:22.340
When she blooms,
she has millions

00:28:22.340 --> 00:28:26.300
of little tiny flowers with
feathery little stigmas

00:28:26.300 --> 00:28:28.290
that are slightly sticky.

00:28:28.290 --> 00:28:32.560
And those stigmas give off
a slight negative electrical

00:28:32.560 --> 00:28:34.790
impulse that's measurable.

00:28:34.790 --> 00:28:36.870
Pollen grains from
a male get in there

00:28:36.870 --> 00:28:39.440
and they tumble
around on the wind.

00:28:39.440 --> 00:28:41.810
They pick up a positive
electrical charge.

00:28:41.810 --> 00:28:44.090
So when you got
positive and negative,

00:28:44.090 --> 00:28:47.430
you have what's called
mutual attraction.

00:28:47.430 --> 00:28:48.700
Boom, pulls it in there.

00:28:48.700 --> 00:28:51.870
Mother nature did not
intend for the pollen just

00:28:51.870 --> 00:28:53.670
to get there by accident.

00:28:53.670 --> 00:28:55.480
She designed it this way.

00:28:55.480 --> 00:28:56.370
Very, very clever.

00:28:56.370 --> 00:28:58.920
But the problem is that
our urban forests are out

00:28:58.920 --> 00:29:00.077
of balance.

00:29:00.077 --> 00:29:02.160
We've got huge amounts of
males and in some plants

00:29:02.160 --> 00:29:05.390
we almost never find
a female anymore.

00:29:05.390 --> 00:29:10.480
I just toss this up because
like if everything else fails,

00:29:10.480 --> 00:29:12.550
there is the basis
for lawsuits now.

00:29:12.550 --> 00:29:14.550
